(11. GENERAL SHIPPING INSTRUCTIONS - For shipments made F.O.B. shipping point: \(a\) All shipments moving in one)SH
1226 951 MT
(day to the same location via the same carrier shall be consolidated on one bill of lading.  Multiple packages in the same)SH
1226 976 MT
(UPS shipment shall be tied into bundles. \(b\) Unless otherwise specifically instructed, shipments via limited liability carriers)SH
1226 1001 MT
(\(AirFreight, UPS, etc.\) and those subject to replacement value ratings shall be declared at the value, which will secure the)SH
1226 1026 MT
(lowest transportation charge. \(c\) Seller shall comply with NBC's shipping and routing instructions. Seller shall not use)SH
1226 1051 MT
(premium cost transportation unless authorized by NBC. \(d\) Losses and/or excess charges resulting from deviation from)SH
1226 1076 MT
(NBC's instructions will be charged to Seller's account.)SH
1226 1126 MT
(12. PROOF OF SHIPMENT - Seller shall forward the receipt or bill of lading signed by the Carrier with Seller's invoice as)SH
1226 1150 MT
(evidence of shipment.  Seller shall receive and retain mailing receipts for uninsured parcel post.)SH
1226 1200 MT
